race.comment: COME TO PARTY (4) hit the frame latest (29.71) when second at Sandown in a Free For All. Has already won two times from this draw. Looks a leading chance on best. CANYA SPEED (6) stalked the lead and fought on well to finish one length away in second (26.11) at this track in a Grade 5 over 460m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Must be included in calculations. CRACKERJACK KEV (8) has a strong overall record having five wins and 12 places from 24 starts but was out of the money last time when fourth (30.25) over 525m at The Meadows. Solid record at the distance winning two races. Best form too dangerous to ignore. Have to include. AS YOU WERE (1) should be thereabouts after filling a top-three spot most recently.
